        <p style="line-height: 1.8; color: #444;">Wood breathes and contracts, leading to moisture and mold. Masonry is inert—it doesn't rot or feed termites. It provides <em>thermal mass</em>, absorbing heat by day and releasing it at night, stabilizing temperatures and reducing AC costs.</p>
